# CSS Best Practices

Writing clean CSS is important for maintainability and scalability.

## 1. Use Meaningful Class Names

Bad:

```css
.red {
    color: red;
}
```

Good:

```css
.error-message {
    color: red;
}
```

## 2. Use External Stylesheets

Bad:

```html
<p style="color:red;">Hello</p>
```

Good:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
```

## 3. Follow Consistent Naming

Example:

```css
.navbar {}
.navbar-logo {}
.navbar-menu {}
```

## 4. Use CSS Variables

```css
:root {
    --primary-color: #007bff;
}
```

## 5. Minimize Repetition

Avoid duplicating styles.

```css
.btn-primary,
.btn-secondary {
    padding: 10px;
}
```

## 6. Organize CSS Properly

Recommended Order:

1. Variables
2. Global Styles
3. Layout
4. Components
5. Utilities

## 7. Optimize Performance

- Remove unused CSS.
- Compress CSS files.
- Minify production stylesheets.

## Summary

Clean CSS improves readability, scalability, and performance.
